HEADWORD: Canellaceae
<hw>Canellaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a natural family
having one genus: aromatic tropical trees of East Africa and Florida to
West Indies.</def> <note>In 1913 the family was classed as an order: see
<er>canella</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Canellaceae</fam>, canella
family.</syn>⟦br⟧
